Talks have occurred between Britain andthe offshore financial centers of the Channel Islands and theIsle of Man aimed at reaching a pact to limit insider dealing,Corporate Affairs Minister Michael Howard said.    He told Parliament in a written answer that "there have beeninformal talks at official level. I would hope, in due course,to arrive at arrangements" along the lines of an agreed policyto curb trading which uses privileged information.    The Channel Islands and the Isle of Man areconstitutionally independent of Britain's parliament, and havefiscal regimes sympathetic to business and the accumulation ofcapital. Reuter&#3;